00:36:36.200 --> 00:36:41.530
If I want c_3, I should
multiply both sides by, should I

00:36:41.530 --> 00:36:45.110
multiply both sides by e^(i3x)?

00:36:45.110 --> 00:36:47.630
Nope.

00:36:47.630 --> 00:36:49.360
e^(-i3x).

00:36:49.360 --> 00:36:54.310
Multiply both sides by
e^(-i3x) and integrate.

00:36:54.310 --> 00:36:57.700
e^(-i3x) d x.

00:36:57.700 --> 00:37:00.880
And then on the right
side I get what?

00:37:00.880 --> 00:37:07.460
I get c_3, because that'll
be e^(-i3x) times e^(+i3x),

00:37:07.460 --> 00:37:14.310
I'll be integrating one so
