00:44:19.510 --> 00:44:22.660
would say this is the
most important inequality

00:44:22.660 --> 00:44:23.940
in mathematics.

00:44:23.940 --> 00:44:36.310
That the dot product
of two vectors,

00:44:36.310 --> 00:44:39.350
it's called the
Schwarz inequality.

00:44:39.350 --> 00:44:43.990
Several people found
it independently,

00:44:43.990 --> 00:44:50.560
Schwarz is the single
name most often used.

00:44:50.560 --> 00:44:55.980
What do you know about the
dot product of two vectors?

00:44:55.980 --> 00:44:58.740
Somehow it tells you the
angle between them, right?

00:44:58.740 --> 00:45:03.800
Somehow the dot
product of two vectors

00:45:03.800 --> 00:45:09.490
is, if I divide by the
length of the vectors,

00:45:09.490 --> 00:45:13.140
so the dot product of vectors
divided by the length,

00:45:13.140 --> 00:45:16.750
do you know what
this is, in geometry?

00:45:16.750 --> 00:45:17.830
It's a cosine.

00:45:17.830 --> 00:45:21.650
It's the cosine of the
angle between them.

00:45:21.650 --> 00:45:25.010
And cosines are never
larger than one.

00:45:25.010 --> 00:45:28.400
So this quantity here is
never larger than one;

00:45:28.400 --> 00:45:30.570
in other words,
this is never larger

00:45:30.570 --> 00:45:33.620
than the length of one
vector times the length

00:45:33.620 --> 00:45:35.890
of the other vector.

00:45:35.890 --> 00:45:37.140
I could do an example.

00:45:37.140 --> 00:45:42.250
